@startuml

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
}
skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    BorderColor #6C757D
}
skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
    BorderColor #495057
    ArrowColor #495057
    FontColor #212529
    DiamondBackgroundColor #E9ECEF
    DiamondBorderColor #6C757D
    StartColor #212529
    EndColor #212529
    BarColor #495057
}
skinparam swimlane {
    BorderColor #6C757D
    TitleBackgroundColor #DEE2E6
    TitleFontColor #212529
    TitleFontSize 13
}

title Image Generation Flow

|Caller|
start
:Call **ImageProvider::image**(\n  prompt, attachments=[], size=null,\n  quality=null, model=null, timeout=null);

|GeneratesImages Trait|
:Generate **invocationId** = Str::uuid7();

if (model param null?) then (yes)
    :Resolve model =\n**defaultImageModel()**\n(e.g. 'grok-2-image' from config);
else (no)
    :Use provided **model**;
endif

:Create **ImagePrompt**(prompt, attachments,\nsize, quality, provider, model);

if (Ai::imagesAreFaked()?) then (yes)
    :Record fake via\n**Ai::recordImageGeneration**(prompt);
    :Return fake **ImageResponse**\n(no HTTP call made);
    |Caller|
    :Receive fake **ImageResponse**;
    stop
else (no)
    :Dispatch event:\n**GeneratingImage**(invocationId, provider, model, prompt);
endif

|HasImageGateway Trait|
:Call **imageGateway()** to\nresolve gateway instance;

if ($imageGateway property set?\n(via useImageGateway)) then (yes)
    :Return **custom ImageGateway**\ninjected at runtime;
else (no)
    :Lazy-create default gateway\n(**XaiImageGateway** or **OpenAiImageGateway**);
endif

|ImageGateway (XAI / OpenAI)|
:Call **generateImage**(provider, model,\nprompt, attachments, size, quality, timeout);

:Set effective **timeout** =\ntimeout ?? **120 seconds**;

:Wrap call in **withErrorHandling**(provider->name(), fn)\n[HandlesFailoverErrors trait];

:Build **HTTP client** via\n**CreatesXaiClient** / **CreatesOpenAiClient**\nusing provider config + timeout;

:Send HTTP request:\n**POST images/generations**\n{ model, prompt, response_format: 'b64_json' };

if (HTTP / API error?) then (yes)
    :**HandlesFailoverErrors**\nhandles exception\n(failover / rethrow);
    |GeneratesImages Trait|
    :Propagate error to Caller;
    |Caller|
    :Receive exception;
    stop
else (no)
    :Call **$response->json()**\nto parse JSON body;
    :Extract image data:\n**$response['data'][0]['b64_json']**;
    :Create **GeneratedImage**(b64_json, 'image/jpeg')\n[base64 string + mime type];
    :Wrap in **Illuminate\\Collection**\n([GeneratedImage]);
    fork
        :Create **Usage** object\n(empty/default for images);
    fork again
        :Create **Meta**(provider->name(), model);
    end fork
    :Return new **ImageResponse**(Collection<GeneratedImage>, Usage, Meta);
endif

|GeneratesImages Trait|
:Receive **ImageResponse** via tap();

:Dispatch event:\n**ImageGenerated**(invocationId, provider,\nmodel, prompt, response);

:Return **ImageResponse** to Caller;

|Caller|
:Receive **ImageResponse**\n(images, usage, meta);
note right
  ImageResponse implements
  Countable + Htmlable;
  images → Collection<GeneratedImage>
end note
stop

@enduml
